During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Sarah Sanders discussed President Trump's school safety plan, which focuses on hardening schools, strengthening background checks, reforming mental health programs, and continuing the conversation on school violence prevention. Sanders also announced that President Trump will welcome Crown Prince Mohammed Bin Salman of Saudi Arabia to the White House on March 20th and will travel to Peru and Colombia next month. In addition, she addressed questions about the upcoming meeting with North Korea, the recent poisoning of a former spy in the UK, and the President's trip to California. Sanders emphasized that the President is focused on pushing through policies that have broad bipartisan support and can be accomplished immediately, while still considering other proposals for further review.